n enkele verplichtingen (= gebruikseisen). </p><p><a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/informatie-voor-de-milieudeskundige-bodemcorrosie\">Meer info over de verplichtingen voor erkende milieudeskundigen</a>. </p>","en-x-generated":"<p>To be recognised as an 'environmental expert on soil corrosion', you must meet:</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36058\">general recognition conditions</a> that apply to all environmental recognitions:<ul><li>In the 3 years preceding the application for the Flemish certificate of recognition, the applicant has not incurred any criminal conviction in a <a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/uw-overheid/verdeling-van-de-bevoegdheden/de-europese-unie-eu-de-europese-economische-ruimte-eer-het-schengengebied-en-de-eurozone\">Member State of the European Economic Area</a> for breaches of environmental legislation relating to the use of the recognition</li><li>in the 2 years preceding the application for the Flemish recognition certificate, no recognition with the same object has been withdrawn from the applicant, for violation of the related obligations of that recognition.</li></ul></li><li>special conditions of recognition:<ul><li>be a <strong>natural person </strong>;</li><li>have obtained at least <strong>the bachelor's degree</strong> from a course listed in <a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36561&amp;woLang=nl\">annex 5 of the VLAREL</a> or an equivalent degree<ul><li>and have at least <strong>1 year of practical experience</strong> in the discipline of soil corrosion, acquired <strong>within 5 years prior</strong> to the application for recognition</li></ul></li><li>or have obtained at least a <strong>secondary school diploma</strong> or an equivalent certificate <ul><li>and at least <strong>5 years of</strong> practical experience in the discipline of soil corrosion, acquired within <strong>10</strong> years prior to the application for recognition. </li></ul></li>