 been convicted of a criminal offence in a member state of the European Economic Area, for infringements of the environmental legislation concerning the use of the recognition.</li><li>in the 2 years that precede the application for the Flemish recognition certificate, no recognition with the same object was revoked due to infringement of the obligations associated with that recognition.</li></ul></li><li><strong>special recognition conditions:</strong><ul><li>be a natural person</li><li>having obtained at least a <strong>master’s </strong>or equivalent degree<ul><li>having at least 3 years’ practical experience in contracts in the field of the recognition, obtained within the 5 years preceding the application for recognition</li></ul></li><li>having obtained at least a <strong>bachelor’s </strong>or equivalent degree<ul><li>having at least 5 years’ practical experience in the field of the recognition, obtained within the 7 years preceding the application for recognition</li></ul></li><li>having successfully completed a <strong>training course</strong> in which the subjects listed in <a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36635&amp;woLang=nl\">annex 9 of the VLAREL</a> are covered.</li></ul></li></ul><h2>Validity period and obligations</h2><p>The recognition is valid for an <strong>indefinite period</strong>. As a recognised ‘environmental expert in noise and vibrations’, you must meet the following obligations among others to retain your recognition:</p><ul><li>each year, undergo <strong>refresher training</strong> of at least 8 hours on the most recent developments and legislation on noise and vibrations for which you are recognised (noise and/or vibrations)</li><li>hold <strong>insurance</strong> for third-party liability, including professional liability, in connection with the use of the recognition</li><li>pay the<a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/vlarel-retributies\"> annual fee</a>. The first payment is to be made in the year following the year in which you obtained the recognition. Failure to pay the annual fee will lead to automatic suspension of the recognition following a formal notice of default. If the fee is not paid within 30 days of the suspension, the recognition will automatically lapse.</li></ul><p><a href=\"https://www.dev-vlaanderen.be/informatie-voor-de-milieudeskundige-geluid-en-trillingen\">More info on the obligations for recognised environmental experts</a> can be found on the Department of Environment and Spatial Development website.</p>","en-x-generated":"<p>To be recognised as an 'environmental expert on noise and vibration', you must meet:</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://navigator.emis.vito.be/mijn-navigator?woId=36058\">general recognition conditions</a> that apply to all environmental recognitions:<ul><li>in the 3 years preceding the application for the Flemish certificate of recognition, the applicant has not been convicted in a Member State of the European Economic Area for breaches of environmental legislation relating to the use of the recognition</li><li>in the 2 years preceding the application for the Flemish recognition certificate, no recognition with the same object has been withdrawn from the applicant, for violation of the related obligations of that recognition.</li></ul></li><li>special conditions of recognition:<ul><li>be a <strong>natural person</strong> </li><li>have obtained at least <strong>a master's degree</strong> or an equivalent degree<ul><li>and have at least <strong>3 years of practical experience </strong>in carrying out assignments under the recognition, acquired <strong>within 5 years prior</strong> to the application for recognition</li></ul></li><li>or have obtained at least <strong>a Bachelor's degree</strong> or an equivalent degree<ul><li>and at least <strong>5 years of practical experience</strong> in carrying out assignments within the scope of recognition, acquired within <strong>7</strong> years prior to the application for recognitio